<subSubSection id="3164F2F20532308A4CEB3E5403869062" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="D2A72743A78CA33D167FFB687F4C7BBE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25577D52AFD4BE19580EC18D8D9D5BC0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Montane forest at 900-2500 m elevation.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="00328D01D56D6FB3B469EC193169A193" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="C7B06182CF1350F0E40C5A8ACC68CD6D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="96478E6F2B690BB4D5C98D1ACCAE9A57" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="38C10920AADD150C920A580C321CF7F3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Dissochaeta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dissochaeta glandiformis" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glandiformis">
<emphasis id="5B85D94AA63A744B349952C03E93707B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Dissochaeta glandiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles to 
<taxonomicName id="038A98CBC3DCDC475A2BE7612C1A5DA5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="D." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. intermedia" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="8D87A20D49D85E6374803B72BE9CDBAD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with brown stellate- tomentose hairs in leaf blades abaxiallyly and having only 4 alternipetalous stamens with two filiform lateral appendages. This species differs from the latter by having a conspicous interpetiolar ridge (annular and crest-like or ligular) at the nodes and longer calyx lobes (2-2.5 mm long). The calyx lobes are distinctly united and have an acorn-like appearance when in bud, splitting into four lobes at maturity (
<bibRefCitation id="1342CBB57B7B699AD8F7957CE9B21674" author="Maxwell, JF" journalOrPublisher="Gardens' Bulletin (Singapore)" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="312 - 327" refId="B44" refString="Maxwell, JF, 1980b. Taxonomic notes on the tribe Dissochaeteae (Naudin) Triana (Melastomataceae). Gardens' Bulletin (Singapore) 33: 312 - 327" title="Taxonomic notes on the tribe Dissochaeteae (Naudin) Triana (Melastomataceae)." volume="33" year="1980 b">Maxwell 1980b</bibRefCitation>
). This species is restricted to the montane forest of the Mount Kerinci complex, Sumatra.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
